input.name: Collection Name
input.narrative: The name of the collection to act upon

field.name: Test
field.description: Shows the name of the test.

field.name: Success?
field.description: Shows if the test succeeded or failed.

field.name: Error message
field.description: If Success = False: Shows error message

input.name: Source
input.narrative: A collection to calculate the All of.

input.name: Predicate
input.narrative: A projection function to apply to each element.

input.name: Parameter
input.narrative: A collection that contains zero or more objects to insert into the predicate as parameters. Similar to the way String.Format formats strings.

output.name: Result
output.narrative: true if every element of the source sequence passes the test in the specified predicate, or if the sequence is empty; otherwise, false.
